      • open

        public void open()
          throws IOException,
                 IllegalArgumentException
        Establishes a connection for the device and IoT Hub/Protocol Gateway given in the client configuration. If the connection is already open, the function shall do nothing.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if connection parameters are null or empty.
        IOException - if a connection could not to be established.

      • close

        public void close()
        Closes the connection. After the connection is closed, it is no longer usable. If the connection is already closed, the function shall do nothing.

        public Message receiveMessage()

      • sendMessageResult

        public void sendMessageResult(IotHubMessageResult result)
                       throws IOException
        Sends the message result for the previously received message.
        Parameters:
        result - the message result (one of IotHubMessageResult.COMPLETE, IotHubMessageResult.ABANDON, or IotHubMessageResult.REJECT).
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if sendMessageResult is called before receiveMessage() is called.
        IOException - if the IoT Hub could not be reached.
